FBIS4-15590 "drsov069_s_94008" FBIS-SOV-94-069 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 Georgia Abkhazia Blames Georgia for Attack on Kodor Abkhazia Blames Georgia for Attack on Kodor LD0804210394 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1828 GMT 8 Apr 94 LD0804210394 Moscow INTERFAX English BFN [Text] The Abkhazian Defense Ministry told Interfax that Georgian troops had been subjecting the populated center of Upper Lata in the Kodor Cave to a second day of artillery fire. Casualties were reported among the civilian population and serious damage to several houses. First Deputy Chairman of the Abkhazian Supreme Soviet, Stanislav Lakoba, said the UN, other international organizations and Russia must respond to Georgia's gross violations of the documents recently signed in Moscow.
